:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"rss\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"rss enclosure\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"rss media\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"http://blog.futtta.be/?p=10331\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:349:\"The standard WordPress RSS-feeds don&#8217;t include posts featured image. Below code adds the medium-format thumbnail to each item in a RSS2 standards-compliant manner by inserting it as an enclosure. A more advanced &#38; flexible approach would be to add support for the media RSS namespace, but the above suffices for the purpose I have in [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2300:\"<p>The standard WordPress RSS-feeds don&#8217;t include posts featured image. Below code adds the medium-format thumbnail to each item in a RSS2 standards-compliant manner by <a href=\"https://validator.w3.org/feed/docs/rss2.html#ltenclosuregtSubelementOfLtitemgt\">inserting it as an enclosure</a>.</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">add_action(\'rss2_item\', \'add_enclosure_thumb\');\nfunction add_enclosure_thumb() {\n  global $post;\n  if(has_post_thumbnail($post-&gt;ID)) {\n    $thumbUrl = get_the_post_thumbnail_url($post-&gt;ID,&quot;medium&quot;);\n\n    if ((substr($thumbUrl, -4) === &quot;jpeg&quot;) || (substr($thumbUrl, -3) === &quot;jpg&quot;)) {\n      $mimeType=&quot;image/jpeg&quot;;\n    } else if (substr($thumbUrl, -3) === &quot;png&quot;) {\n      $mimeType=&quot;image/png&quot;;\n    } else if (substr($thumbUrl, -3) === &quot;gif&quot;) {\n      $mimeType=&quot;image/gif&quot;;\n    } else {\n      $mimeType=&quot;image/unkown&quot;;\n    }\n\n    $thumbSize = filesize(WP_CONTENT_DIR.str_replace(WP_CONTENT_URL,\'\',$thumbUrl));\n\n    echo &quot;&lt;enclosure url=\\&quot;&quot;.$thumbUrl.&quot;\\&quot; size=\\&quot;&quot;.$thumbSize.&quot;\\&quot; type=\\&quot;&quot;.$mimeType.&quot;\\&quot; /&gt;\\n&quot;;\n  }\n}</pre>\n<p>A more advanced &amp; flexible approach would be to add support for <a href=\"http://www.rssboard.org/media-rss\">the media RSS namespace</a>, but the above suffices for the purpose I have in mind.</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/2012/07/10/stopping-wordpress-media-attachments-comment-spam/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Stopping WordPress media attachments comment spam\">Stopping WordPress media attachments comment spam </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/2014/11/21/force-akismet-to-permanently-delete-spam-meta-sooner/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"I see you baby, purging that spam!\">I see you baby, purging that spam! </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/2014/10/22/tweaking-wordpresss-expound-theme-menu/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Tweaking WordPress&#8217;s Expound theme&#8217;s menu\">Tweaking WordPress&#8217;s Expound theme&#8217;s menu </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/iQnGZb9juxI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" 